headline: Another Lockheed Martin-Built GPS III Satellite Lifts Off into Orbit
summary: At 1:37 p.m. EDT today, the eighth GPS III space vehicle—designed and built by Lockheed Martin (NYSE: LMT) —successfully launched from Cape Canaveral Space Force Station, Florida. It achieved signal acquisition shortly thereafter.

headline: Lockheed Martin Wins $509M Contract for GPS III Satellite Project
summary: LMT secures $509M Air Force contract to build GPS III satellites with advanced anti-jamming technology, boosting its space and defense leadership.
